<FILEID>AP-NR-01-18-89 0613EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a BC-Quotes     01-18 0190</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Quotes,0194</SECOND>
<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``I don't understand why and I probably won't ever know why. It
troubles me to think that such a terrible thing can happen. It's
like a nightmare. This sort of thing happens to others, not you.
Your own grandson.'' _ Julia Chumbley reacting to news that her
grandson, Patrick Edward Purdy, sprayed a Stockton, Calif.,
schoolyard full of children with gunfire, killing five and wounding
30, before killing himself.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``In order to enforce order in the marketplace, we must be
brutally violent to innocent people.'' _ An Israeli army reservist
who identified himself only as Yotam, joining other reservists in
complaining bitterly to Prime Minister Yitzhak Shamir about the way
they are ordered to treat Palestinians.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``The talk is different, but the force structure and policies
that support far-reaching interests and clients have not changed
commensurately. Many of those policies and those clients are hostile
to American values and threaten our interests and our allies. That's
a reality.'' _ Secretary of State-designate James A. Baker III
giving his view of the Soviet Union to the Senate Foreign Relations
Committee.
