<FIRST>r a PM-OvertownChronology     01-18 0551</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Overtown Chronology,0576</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Overtown Riot, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a chronology detailing the eruption of
racial violence in Miami:
</TEXT>
<NOTE>MONDAY:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   _6:05 p.m, off-duty police Officer John Mervolion is sitting in a
marked patrol car when he spots two black men on a motorcycle
speeding northbound from downtown into the Overtown area.
   Mervolian, 34, turns on his blue lights and chases the
motorcycle, but the driver, Clement Anthony Lloyd, 23, doesn't stop,
said police spokesman Raymond Lang.
   Mervolian, a seven-year police veteran, calls for assistance on
his police radio. Three blocks away, Officer William Lozano is
filling out a crime report when he hears the call and realizes the
motorcycle was heading toward him.
   Lozano, 29, fires once, hitting Lloyd in the head, Lang said. The
bike veers across the center line and smashes into a car. Lloyd is
pronounced dead at the scene. His passenger, Allen Blanchard, 24, is
taken to Jackson Memorial Hospital in critical condition.
   _7:30 p.m., Mayor Xavier Suarez and City Manager Cesar Odio
arrive at the scene with more police and attempt to calm the rapidly
growing crowd.
   _8 p.m., police officers, reporters and city officials are
surrounded and retreat under a hail of rocks and bottles.
   _8:20 p.m., all off-duty officers and police supervisors are
called in as mobs of youths begin roaming the streets, smashing
windshields, burning vehicles, looting some stores and occasionally
firing weapons.
   _Shortly before 10 p.m., police in riot gear fire tear gas and
then withdraw to a 17-by-9-block perimeter.
   _Midnight, police say most of the area is calm.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>TUESDAY:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   _Morning, police suspend Lozano, a four-year-veteran, with pay
pending an investigation into whether he used excessive force.
   _1:30 p.m., a white man in a luxury car fires into a crowd of
blacks in Overtown and drives away. Derrick Mitchell, 19, is
hospitalized in fair condition with a bullet wound in his side.
   _4:10 p.m., Blanchard dies at Jackson Memorial Hospital of head
injuries from the collision, hospital officials say.
   _5 p.m., police in Overtown shoot an alleged sniper in the leg.
   _7 p.m., a man is shot in the thigh in a gun battle between two
men in a store and a gang of looters, authorities said. Police were
fired upon as they try to rescue him but manage to get him out.
   _8 p.m., police tell residents of Overtown and Liberty City to
remain indoors and begin a block-by-block sweep of the area.
   _8:15 p.m., police return fire at another Liberty City man who
was apparently firing at police. Police say the man is wounded in
the leg but release no further details.
   _8:45 p.m., widespread looting and fires are reported at stores
in Liberty City.
   _9:30 p.m., Police Officer Eric Butler is shot in his bulletproof
vest by a sniper firing from the top of a three-story building.
   _10:20 p.m., a young black man is shot to death and an arrest in
made in Liberty City.
   _10:50 p.m., a person is shot three times by an unknown assailant
on the fringe of Liberty City.
   _11:10 p.m., a man is shot in the leg in Liberty City.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>WEDNESDAY:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   _12:30 a.m. 230 arrests are made as the sound of gunfire
continues in Liberty City.
   _Toward dawn, calm enables police to ease its presence in
Overtown and Liberty City.
</TEXT>
