<SECOND>PM-Malaysia,0181</SECOND>
<HEAD>Prime Minister Hospitalized With Chest Pains</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad was
hospitalized today after he complained of chest pains, an official
said.
   ``His condition is stable and satisfactory,'' said Dr. C Fonseka,
director of the Government Hospital, where the 63-year-old leader
was taken.
   Mahathir became Malaysia's prime minister in 1981 after serving
as deputy prime minister since 1976.
   Relatives and close friends of Mahathir said he had had minor
blood pressure problems in the past, but that this was the first
time he was hospitalized with chest pains.
   Government officials said they canceled an afternoon meeting
between Mahathir and Prime Minister Choonhavan Chatichai of Thailand.
   Chatichai arrived today for a two-day visit, during which he is
to attend the 33rd General Border Committee meeting. Thailand and
Malaysia hold the meetings from time to time to review their fight
against 1,500 communist guerrillas operating along a common border.
   Mahathir has been criticized for curbing the powers of the
judiciary and press, but politicians and diplomats say he remains
powerful.
