<HEAD>Pope Calls For Prayers For Vatican Council Anniversary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II on Wednesday called for
prayers for Christian unity to mark the 30th anniversary of the
Second Vatican Council.
   In remarks to his weekly general audience, John Paul said
divisions among Christians were ``contrary to the will of the Lord.''
   He said he would go to the Basilica of St. Paul's Outside the
Walls on Jan. 25 to recall the Jan. 25, 1959, announcement by Pope
John XXIII of an ecumenical council for the church.
   The council, called the Second Vatican Council, was opened by
Pope John in 1962 and paved the way for the Roman Catholic Church's
efforts to improve relations with other Christian denominations.
