<DOCNO> AP890118-0126 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-01-18-89 1228EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Denmark-Arson     01-18 0124</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Denmark-Arson,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Found Guilty of Arson That Killed 35</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mentally retarded man was convicted
Wednesday of setting a fire at a Copenhagen hotel in 1973 that
killed 35 people.
   The city court in nearby Hilleroed also found Erik Hansen guilty
of killing a 15-year-old girl in 1980 as she sunbathed on a beach in
western Denmark, according to the report on state-run television.
   Hansen, 40, confessed to both crimes.
   He first admitted setting fire to the hotel after he was arrested
last year in a series of arsons in the Copenhagen area that killed
two people. Hansen confessed to the slaying in 1did
