<HEAD>Athlete Begins Cross-Country Fund-Raiser</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A disabled athlete rolled away from City Hall
in his wheelchair Tuesday, embarking on 5,000-mile, 20-state trek to
raise money for paralysis research.
   ``I want people to realize that living with a disability does not
limit one's ability to live life to the fullest,'' said Bill Duff,
26, a Houston native who was paralyzed from the waist down in a car
accident seven years ago.
   As a Dixieland band played, four motorcycle officers escorted
Duff as he headed out of the city on a trip that he hopes will wind
up in New York in July.
   Dozens of corporations have helped fund Duff's Wheels Across
America journey. Project organizers hope he will inspire
contributions to the Miami Project to Cure Paralysis, a program
sponsored by the University of Miami.
