<FILEID>AP-NR-01-18-89 1422EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r w PM-Reagan-Medals 2ndLd-Writethru a0647-a061Guyton 01-18
0281</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Reagan-Medals, 2nd Ld-Writethru, a0647-a0619,250</SECOND>
<HEAD>President Decorates GOP Leaders of Congress</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Top 6 grafs with recipients, nature of medal; picks up pvs 3rd
graf, ``Reagan said''</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan presented the Citizens Medal
today to 38 people ranging from movie actor Charlton Heston to the
late Ambassador to Pakistan Arnold L. Raphel and including three
leading congressional Republicans.
   The awards to Senate Minority Leader Bob Dole, House Minority
Leader Robert Michel and Sen. Strom Thurmond, former president pro
tempore of the Senate and the chamber's senior member, were made at
a ceremony in the Cabinet Room, with reporters present.
   The other awards were made in the East Room to which reporters
were not admitted.
   The Citizens Medal is awarded to recognize U.S. citizens who have
performed exemplary deeds or service for their country or their
fellow citizens.
   Raphel was killed last Aug. 17 in the crash of a military
transport plane that also took the life of Pakistan's President
Mohammad Zia ul-Haq.
   In the public ceremony, Reagan said of Dole, the senior senator
from Kansas and a combat veteran of World War II: ``Whether on the
battlefield or Capitol Hill, Senate Robert Dole has served America
heroically.''
   Reagan said Michel, a representative from Illinois, was ``the man
who could always be counted on by his president, his constituents
and his country.''
   Turning to Thurmond, the Republican senator from South Carolina,
the president said, ``He worked to appoint conservative judges and
strong proponents of constitutional law.''
   Thurmond responded, ``I appreciate this, coming from the finest
president since George Washington.''
   The medal recipients were accompanied by their families.
   White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said Reagan personally
selected the recipients.
</TEXT>
