<SECOND>AM-Obit-DuVal-Lewis, CORRECTIVE, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0696,0178</SECOND>
<UNK>Eds: Subs 3rd graf, `Tracing the ...,' to CORRECT that Wiliam Henry
Harrison was nation's ninth, sted 10th, president. Members who used a0617-a0783,
a Tucson, Ariz.-dated story sent Jan. 11 slugged Obit-DuVal-Lewis, are
asked to use the following story.</UNK>
<DATELINE>TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press erroneously reported on
Jan. 11 that Irene DuVal-Lewis, who died on Jan. 9 at 105, was a
granddaughter of President Benjamin Harrison and had resided or
spent extensive time in the White House as a child.
   A check of the Benjamin Harrison family tree found no trace of
Mrs. DuVal-Lewis or of her mother, Oliva Harrison, through whom Mrs.
DuVal-Lewis had said the presidential kinship came.
   Tracing the family lines of that president's grandfather, William
Henry Harrison, who was the nation's ninth president, and other
forebears back to the Benjamin Harrison who signed the Declaration
of Independence, also produced no link with Mrs. DuVal-Lewis.
   Mrs. DuVal-Lewis also was not among those who resided in the
White House or spent extensive time there, according to White House
records.
