<SECOND>AM-China-Collision,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>At Least 32 Die In Train-Bus Collision</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger train crashed into a bus Wednesday at
an unguarded rail crossing in northeast China, killing at least 32
people and injuring 41 aboard the bus, an official report said.
   The Xinhua News Agency said it had no word of any casualties
among people on the train.
   The train was traveling in Huinan County in Jilin province when
it collided with the bus, pushing it about 90 feet up the track,
Xinhua said. The front car of the train was derailed, it said.
   The accident was similar to two others in the past month in
northeast China.
   Thirty-one people were killed, including members of a bridal
party, when a freight train collided with a bus Jan. 1 in
Heilongjiang province, north of Jilin.
   Forty-six people died and 67 were injured when a train in
Liaoning province, south of Jilin, collided with a bus on Dec. 23.
