guilders, up from 2.0855; 1,361.00 (1,363.75) Italian lire, up from
1,354.00; 1.1966 (1.1975) Canadian dollars, down from 1.1973.
   In Tokyo, where trading ends before Europe's business day begins,
the dollar rose 0.20 yen to a closing 127.90 yen. Later, in London,
it was quoted at 127.50 yen after the trade report and 127.95 yen
before.
   Gold opened in London at a bid price of $402.80 a troy ounce, up
from $402.25 late Tuesday. At midmorning, London bullion dealers
fixed a recommended price of $402.85 a troy ounce.
   In Zurich, gold was trading at a bid $403.05 compared with
$402.15 bid late Tuesday.
   Earlier, in Hong Kong, gold rose 21 cents to close at a bid
$404.64.
   Silver bullion prices rose on the London market, where the metal
was trading at a bid price of $5.94 a troy ounce, compared with
Tuesday's $5.92.
