<FIRST>r f PM-Recall-Autos     01-18 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Recall-Autos,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Audi Recalls 35,000 5000 Turbos for Fuel Injector Problems</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Audi of America Inc. is recalling about 35,000
1984-1988 5000 Turbo and a small number of 1989 Turbo cars because
of a fuel injection system problem that could cause an engine fire.
   Audi spokesman Joseph Bennett said the company was aware of about
a dozen such fires, resulting in no injuries or accidents.
   The company said Tuesday that high temperature and alcohol in
some fuels may harden injector seals, allowing fuel to escape into
the engine compartment and causing a fire.
   Audi will notify owners of affected vehicles during the next
week. Replacement parts will be available beginning early next month
and repairs will be performed free of charge, the automaker said.
</TEXT>
