<FILEID>AP-NR-01-18-89 2231EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f AM-Earns-Ameritech     01-18 0199</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Ameritech,0208</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ameritech's Profit Up 4.1 Percent in 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ameritech Inc., citing the popularity of cellular
phones and a big increase in new phone lines, on Wednesday reported
a 4.1 percent rise in net income during 1988 to $1.24 billion.
   Revenue during the year increased 3.7 percent to $9.9 billion,
the company said.
   ``Revenue growth reflects an increase of 375,000 Ameritech Bell
company customer lines, up 2.5 percent over the prior year _ the
largest increase in our history,'' said William L. Weiss, Ameritech
chairman and chief executive officer.
   Ameritech is the parent of Bell telephone companies serving
Illinois, Indiana, Michigan, Ohio and Wisconsin.
   The 1988 results also reflect growth at an Ameritech arm, the
Ameritech Enterprise Group.
   The unit reported a 14 percent increase in revenue, due mostly to
a 68 percent increase in cellular lines, to more than 146,000.
   Adjusted for a 2-for-1 stock split, Ameritech earnings per share
in 1988 were $4.55, up from $4.24 in 1987.
   Net income for the fourth quarter was $309.7 million, down from
$322.2 million for the same period in 1987. The company said
fourth-quarter revenue was reduced by higher expenses and the
absence of divested operations.
</TEXT>
