<FIRST>u f AM-SmokelessCigarette     01-18 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Smokeless Cigarette,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pharmacy Board Votes That Premier a Cigarette, Not Regulatable</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Arizona Board of Pharmacy voted
Wednesday to define R.J. Nabisco Inc.'s new Premier ``smokeless''
tobacco product as a cigarette, beyond its power to regulate sales,
despite critics' wishes to label it a drug-delivery device.
   The board also reiterated its request of two months ago that
Nabisco voluntarily withdraw Premier from Arizona test markets, as
well as its call for a rapid decision by the U.S. Food and Drug
Administration on whether the product is a cigarette, as Nabisco
says, or a drug-related system.
   The company again declined.
   ``We would not withdraw the product from the market based on a
request from the Arizona Board of Pharmacy,'' said Betsy Annese, a
company spokeswoman in Winston-Salem, N.C.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
